HSM.definition:
Physical network attached devices that can be used for the storage of sensitive data (i.e. security keys):
* HW device that manages and safeguards the cryptographic authentication process;
* Partner (Thales) product offered via Ericsson Supply Hub in Sweden due to export restrictions;
* Luna HSM comes in one of two authentication types:
   - Password authenticated (Luna series A)
   - Multi-factor authenticated (also called PED-authenticated for Luna series S).

